      <p>Common (up to 12% population). Twice as common in women.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="flashcard_title sub">Pathology</div>
    <div class="flashcard_copy">
      <p>Not known. Possibly related to dilation/constriction of <strong>cerebral blood vessels</strong> and <strong>calcitonin gene related peptide</strong>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="flashcard_title sub">Top three causes</div>
    <div class="flashcard_copy">
      <p>50% have precipitants (<em>chocolate, oral contraceptive, cheese, caffeine, alcohol, exercise</em>)</p>
    </div>

